No-Intro: 2 in 1 - Block Buster + Cross High (USA, Europe)
2 in 1 - Hash Blocks + Eagle Plan (USA, Europe)
TOSEC: 2 in 1 - Hash Blocks + Eagle Plan (1992)(Bon Treasure)

No-Intro: Kabi Island - Gold in Island (USA, Europe)

1.en: A little boy is confused in a world of bubbles where he will have to learn to distinguish the edible bubbles from foreign bubbles which can cause damage to the boy.

2.en: Challenger Tank is a vertically-scrolling action game similar to Ikari Warriors. The player controls a tank which moves continually forward, and can freely move about the screen firing in any direction; the tank's cannon can be rotated independently of its movement. Enemy tanks appear from all sides, shooting at the player, and must be destroyed or avoided. At the end of each stage, a large boss appears that must be defeated to continue. Power-ups will occasionally appear that will allow the tank to fire in multiple directions simultaneously, but these are lost if the tank takes a hit.

3.en: Climbers are always dreaming of climbing the Mount Everest.  If you are one of them, you must enjoy this adventure game which gives you the same feeling as climbing.

4.en: Crystball is a Breakout clone in the tradition of Arkanoid. The player controls a paddle at the bottom of the screen, and must bounce a ball off the bricks on the screen, with the goal of destroying them all. Destroying certain bricks will release power-ups or release enemies that wander the screen. If the ball falls out the bottom of the screen, a life is lost, and if all lives are lost, the game is over.

5.en: Our hero Wei-Wei has taken up the meaningful task to recover a long lost treasure.  Help him to find all hidden money, defeat the enemy, the poisonous spiders, and exit TAIJI alive!

6.en: There is always a belief that living creatures exists outside the solar system.  And scientists are afraid that they would invade the earth.  Hence, they have designed a robot in preparation for future attacks.  This robot called Earth Defender is put in action at last and you are invited to defend the earth with the guns provided.

7.en: A space battle breaks out in the galaxy.  You are now engaged in this fast moving, shooting game.  You are the pilot of a fatal craft which may carry a variety of weapons that will boost your confidence in this battle.

8.en: Final Combat is a top-view tank action game similar to Namco's Battle City. Each stage contains a large number of enemy units and other objects to destroy. The goal is to destroy the fortified enemy base in each area, though the base cannot be damaged until enough enemy units -- tanks and turrets -- are destroyed. When the OK is given, destroy the base to complete the stage. If the player's tank takes too much damage, it will be destroyed.

9.en:
Your starship is alive! A metamorphic creature that can transform from a huge flying insect into a metallic destroyer. Face squadron after squadron of alien fighters, marching ever onward towards a final confrontation with an all-powerful enemy.

This is basically a scrolling, shoot-it-if-it-moves, action game. As your ship scrolls up the screen, you fire on ships coming from the top of the screen. Occasionally, after ships have been destroyed, you can pick up a power up to increase your firing ability. At the end of each level is a boss you must defeat to move onward.

10.en: Some Anti-government Taiki gangsters had a military centre in an island of South America.  They have been organizing Anti-government riots in various cities.  The International Military Union thus orders a spy coded as "Hero Hawk" to ruin the head of the military.

11.en: The health organization was launching a cleaning campaign in kitchens.  A cook who was a committed member of this campaign engaged himself in this kitchen war.  Help him to clear the kitchen thoroughly.

12.en: Little Lap wants to be the number one fighter in the world.  Thus, after he has learned Kung-Fu for thirteen years, he establishes a Kung-Fu platform and invites all fighters to join.

13.en: Linear Racing is a video puzzle game. A short animation is shown, then scrambled into 16 tiles, which must be rearranged to recreate the original image. Tiles may be swapped around, as well as flipped vertically or horizontally, to rebuild the animation. There are six different animations to choose from, and three difficulty settings for each.

14.en: The Sayatians began their invasion of Earth by secretly replacing humans in the military and political posts with Extra Intelligent Beings (EIBs).  To counter this plot, human scientists created a Biochemical Defender whose goal is to eliminate all EIBs.

15.en: The Matta Blatta warship is about to engage in a seas battle and wipe out the enemy fleet.  Join the challenging mission by going on board.  Be sure to power-up your warship and witness the victory of Matta Blatta!

16.en: This is a puzzle game.  Player should arrange the configuration of the falling blocks so as to form a horizontal rectangular block which will disappear automatically.  Otherwise, the blocks will accumulate and increase in height and the game will be over when it reaches the too height limit.

17.en:
Space Fighter is an action shooting game starring a team of three robot soldiers, who must defend their cities from an enemy robot army. Each stage consists of a small scrolling top-down map filled with enemy robots. The player must shoot and destroy a certain number of enemies on each stage in order to move on to the next.

There are three different robots to choose from, each with their own different abilities. HUNT is the quickest, but can only shoot straight forward; DALE is the slowest but has a powerful spread shot; and OWEN is average pm speed, but can fire in four directions simultaneously. On each stage, there is also a base that can be used to switch robots and refill their energy.

18.en:
Sssnake is a basic Snake game. The player controls a snake in a small room filled with food and obstacles. The goal is to eat all the food while avoiding the obstacles, but whenever the snake eats a piece of food, it grows longer, making it more difficult to maneuver. The snake moves forward at a constant speed and can be turned in the four cardinal directions. Holding a button will make the snake move faster, making it harder to control, but increasing the potential for a time bonus.

In this particular version, there are a number of apples on each stage. When an apple is eaten, it disappears, and an apple core appears elsewhere on the stage, and when the apple core is eaten, a deadly skull appears somewhere else. The player must eat all of the apples and apple cores in one run; they will all be reset if the snake touches an obstacle. The player will also earn bonus points if all the normal apples are eaten before any apple core is eaten.

19.en: Tennis Pro '92 is a sports game developed by Bits Studios and was released for Watara Supervision on 12/30/1992

20.en: The universe armour finds a planet suitable for human beings to live in.  And it is going to transfer some people to this planet.  However, people must successfully avoid the galactic strangers and kill the space creatures before it can aboard.

21.en: On the 24th century, a calamity struck as evil spirits, demons, and various monsters appeared from nowhere and started attacking humans.  You, our hero, are our last hope.  Your mission: to defeat these unfriendly hosts and liberate our people from their tyrannical rule.
